<br>
Social Name:<br>
<!--EZCODE FONT START--><span style="color:teal;">CH</span><!--EZCODE FONT END--><br>
<br>
/sit off<br>
/cast 3<br>
/gs CH on [ %T ], hang in there!<br>
/cast 3<br>
<br>
That way if you fizzle on the first try, you try again.  You tend to get an annoying, spammy &quot;you're already casting&quot; type message if you don't fizzle, but for me it's worth it.  Also, just make sure you're not using Tab, etc to switch targets while casting until the 2nd /cast 3 if the first one fizzles.  Sometimes both fizzle and you have to cast again but it's rare.  Just also be ready to duck to cancel twice if you start a CH and decide right away to cancel, because you might cancel the first /cast 3, but then the 2nd one can start. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
Also, don't put /cast 3 on consecutive lines, because the delay between two consecutive lines in a social macro thingee is not enough for recasting a spell after a fizzle.  You need at least one other line in between.<br>
<br>
Hehe, Elhana, I feel your pain on deciding.  I just keep finding more I want, hehe.  I think maybe even with 400 points I'd still want more for certain things.  Oh well, it's good to always have a goal to work for, I guess. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
