 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon3.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showUserPublicProfile?gid=jeninaicemyst>Jenina Icemyst</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 91<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(8/26/03 7:11 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm45.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=89.topic&index=32>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Purify/Remove</span><hr size=1> Post above listed the facts on the two AA.  The following is my opinion and subject to change on a whim or upon reading someone else's post with a better opinion.  <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
Radiant Cure is a must have, at least at level one.  It is way too good for two points to pass up.  I currently have RC2 and plan to get RC3 but I'm not in a huge hurry.  The amount of benefit you get for the extra 10 points isn't even double what you got for your original two points.  The only place I can really tell the difference between RC1 and RC2 is when I'm trying to strip root/snare/ect.  The extra two chances to remove detrimental do make a difference.  For those that don't know, the Remove Detramental line seems to be a random chance to strip a non cureable detramental effect.  Only ones I can think of atm are root, darkness, and malo but I'm sure there are more.<br>
<br>
Purify soul... I'm torn.  I can think of places and times where it would be really nice to know that you are guaranteed to cure everything in one cast.  But, with a 30 minute reuse (which was just today lowered from 72) you are still only able to use it once per raid so it is at best situational.  In another 50ish AA when I run out of things I really want, I'll consider this one again. <p>[65 Archon] <a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=231627">Ariene</a> (High Elf) < Lethal Intent > Bristlebane<BR>
[62 Oracle] <a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=284752">Jenina</a> (Barbarian) < Lethal Intent > Bristlebane<br>
