1)  Max hitpoints<br>
2)  Lung capacity<br>
3)  Stamina bar (ie, the jump-o-meter)<br>
<br>
As for the other things you listed, the STA stat has no effect.  The stamina bar (jump-o-meter) *might*, but unless you have an affinity for fighting underwater or swinging a very heavy hammer, that aught not really be an issue.<br>
<br>
As for what general AA to get, I suggest Run3 and Metabolism3. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showUserPublicProfile?gid=taldaydarfv>Taldaydar FV</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>/join cyberwithtald<br>Useful Posts: 23</span><br>  Posts: 1086<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(10/2/03 5:28 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm45.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=89.topic&index=38>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: My take</span><hr size=1> Penrif knows what he is talking about... what he said about STA is spot on.<br>
